  "title": "UAT Software Test Analyst (Bank Sector Client - Wholesale Banking Applications)",
  "description": "<p><u>About the department</u></p>\n<p>Be part of our clients banking applications quality assurance &amp; software testing team ensuring seamless implementation of technology changes through effective Testing, Training and Documentation. Banking product verticals supported are Cash/ Payments/ Trade / Loans/ Digital Banking Channels </p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u>Your key responsibilities includes:</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>     Handle Manual/ Automated Test Execution (using TOSCA/ other Bank Approved tool) as per the UAT Plan in line with the test strategy and test plan</li>\n  <li>     Ensure all test scope and test cases are executed and fulfil the specified requirements within the agreed timeline</li>\n  <li>     Report defects discovered in UAT, attend defect calls and participate in defect management process and retest</li>\n  <li>     Review UAT test results and publish test metrics</li>\n  <li>     Ensure UAT artifacts and sign-offs are saved as the UAT audit trail</li>\n  <li>     Provide operational readiness support and conduct training on new system/ enhancement to impacted operations and/ or business users</li>\n  <li>     Provide post-implementation support to operations users</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Job Requirements</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>          Bachelor’s degree preferably in Computer Science</li>\n  <li>     Fresher or experience preferably in financial institutions</li>\n  <li>     Experience in operations especially Swift standard in either Cash Management/ Trade Finance/ Loans/ Channels will be an added advantage</li>\n  <li>     Proficient computer skills or programming skills</li>\n  <li>     Experience in automation using tools like TOSCA, Selenium, Appium</li>\n  <li>     Strong analytical skills</li>\n  <li>     Good communication and interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>     Able to work independently and in a team</li>\n  <li>     Motivated driven and can work under pressure and able to complete task given within the project timeline</li>\n  <li>     Have a strong organization belonging, team player and willing to share knowledge</li>\n  <li>     Positive attitude, willingness to learn and motivated to find solutions to the problem</li>\n</ul>",
